money and politics intersect with design, profoundly shaping our everyday experience of city life. Even as she celebrates Philadelphia’s resurgence, she considers how it finds itself grappling with the problems of success: gentrification, poverty, privatization, and the unequal distribution of public services. What emerges in these 80 pieces is a remarkable narrative of a remarkable time. The proverbial first draft of history, these columns tell the story of how a great city shape-shifted before our very eyes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aArchitecture and societyzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aArchitecture and societyzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy21st century. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh  a21st century, Next Detroit, Philadelphia Inquirer, gentrification, poverty, privatization, unequal distribution, Art, Music, Architecture, History: US, Urban Studies, American Studies, General Interest, Regional, Rebuilding, Equitable City, Success, Mega-Projects, Becoming Philadelphia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2020z9783110704679oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069033040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197880067040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978800670423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/97